adjectives.description: backstreet (comparative more backstreet, superlative most backstreet)

entries.meaning: Associated with neighborhoods on back streets, often in older neighborhoods, with poorer residents.
examples: The agency was given to some deserving politician who, as he knew nothing at all about Indians and spoke no language except traces of back-street American, would not be prejudiced in Indian affairs and interfere with the highly informed traders.

entries.meaning: (figuratively) Done in poor and unsanitary conditions, secretly and illegally; back-alley.
examples: The results of self-induced and backstreet abortions come to our hospitals for the damage to be put right.
